From: Dan Carpenter <dan.carpenter@linaro.org>
Date: Tue, 11 Jul 2023 11:21:13 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] accel/qaic: Fix a leak in map_user_pages()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.4.7
Git-commit: 73274c33d961f4aa0f968f763e2c9f4210b4f4a3

commit 73274c33d961f4aa0f968f763e2c9f4210b4f4a3 upstream.

If get_user_pages_fast() allocates some pages but not as many as we
wanted, then the current code leaks those pages.  Call put_page() on
the pages before returning.

Fixes: 129776ac2e38 ("accel/qaic: Add control path")
Signed-off-by: Dan Carpenter <dan.carpenter@linaro.org>
Reviewed-by: Pranjal Ramajor Asha Kanojiya <quic_pkanojiy@quicinc.com>
Reviewed-by: Jeffrey Hugo <quic_jhugo@quicinc.com>
Reviewed-by: Dafna Hirschfeld <dhirschfeld@habana.ai>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org # 6.4.x
Signed-off-by: Jeffrey Hugo <quic_jhugo@quicinc.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/ZK0Q+ZuONTsBG+1T@moroto
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/accel/qaic/qaic_control.c | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/accel/qaic/qaic_control.c b/drivers/accel/qaic/qaic_control.c
index 5c57f7b4..d652b459 100644
--- a/drivers/accel/qaic/qaic_control.c
+++ b/drivers/accel/qaic/qaic_control.c
@@ -418,9 +418,12 @@ static int find_and_map_user_pages(struct qaic_device *qdev,
 	}
 
 	ret = get_user_pages_fast(xfer_start_addr, nr_pages, 0, page_list);
-	if (ret < 0 || ret != nr_pages) {
-		ret = -EFAULT;
+	if (ret < 0)
 		goto free_page_list;
+	if (ret != nr_pages) {
+		nr_pages = ret;
+		ret = -EFAULT;
+		goto put_pages;
 	}
 
 	sgt = kmalloc(sizeof(*sgt), GFP_KERNEL);
